Stanley Roth named as State Dept ' s Asia secretary . President Bill Clinton on Friday nominated Stanley Roth , a former National Security Council official , as assistant secretary of state for East Asian and Pacific affairs , the White House announced . If confirmed by the Senate , Roth will replace Winston Lord , who retired in January . Roth , whose nomination had long been expected , headed Asia policy at the NSC from March 1994 to Jan . 1 , 1996 . Since then he has been a researcher at the U . S . Institute of Peace , a private think - tank . White House Press Secretary Mike McCurry called him " a very capable and skilled foreign policy expert on Asian affairs " . Meanwhile the Senate on Friday confirmed two other State Department nominations : Thomas Pickering , former ambassador to Moscow , as Under Secretary of State for Political Affairs , replacing Peter Tarnoff ; and Stuart Eizenstat , Under Secretary of Commerce for International Trade , as Under Secretary of State for Economic Affairs , replacing Joan Spero . Both appointments were approved by unanimous consent , without a recorded vote . 
